
***** VAR_IMAGE.tx *****

rule(s):
1. commande -> VAR_IMAGE '.' identifier

description:
if the identifier is the string "tx" 
then return the image size along X coordinates.
If the identifier is "ty", return the Y size,
and for "tz" returns the Z size.


Example(s):

print "image size :"; print i.tx; 
print " , ";  print i.ty; 
print " , ";  print i.tz;
print "\n"; 


